	<div class="text">
		<h5>the problem</h5>
		<p>
			The problem is not music. I love listening to all sorts of music genres, whether it is the comforting strum of guitar or mind-numbing bass of who-knows-what. Music can facilitate my mood and inspire me to appreciate the humdrum buzz of the world around me. Music is about emotion through the ether of rhythm and harmony.
		</p>
		<p>
			The problem is the current way music is shared. The popular methods of music dissemination do not allow me to express what a particular song means to me — the emphasis is on the artist and song, not my relationship to it.
		</p>
		<h5>the goal</h5>
		<p>
			Design a website that puts musical connection first — sharing music with those I care about.
		</p>
		<h5>market research</h5>
		<p>
			Music streaming is a big business. Platforms such as Youtube and Spotify allow instant access to a plethora of music. Music-search websites such as Pandora and always-advancing algorithms allow someone to find similar songs to ones they like.
		</p>
		<p>
			Soundcloud is a personal favorite for finding new music. I am able to subscribe to music curators who repost favorite tracks. I know a friend who gained over 200k plays on one of his songs through Soundcloud — showing you don’t have to be a big name to get your music out there and listened to. However, Soundcloud's comments section is an afterthought — just a few tiny words that buzz by as the song plays.
		</p>
		<p>
			I’ve found that the easiest way of sharing music with my friends is to post a link of the song on my Facebook wall. However, the entire post is often lost under the myriad of random other content on Facebook (cough, cough, memes).
		</p>
	</div>

