	<div class="text">
		<h5>back to the drawing board…</h5>
		<p>
			After some quality critique, I realized that the current song module does not emphasize musical connection. Instead, the song and album cover is most prominent.
		</p>
		<p>
			How could I return the focus to the musical experience? By organizing the content in the opposite fashion. So I shifted the focus from the song to the comments. I also realized that the album cover doesn’t mean a whole lot to most people, so instead I replaced it with a visual representation of the emotional quality of the song. The user can choose from a variety of emotional genres such as “rainy mood,” “chill,” or “head-nod.” These icons and matching colors become the visual representation of the song. They give the listener a hint of what they are about to listen to, regardless of whether or not they know of the artist. This also prevents the listener from skipping to songs they are familiar with, because the artist and song are not so prominent within the module.
		</p>
	</div>

