	<div class="text">
		<h5>another round of feedback</h5>
		<p>
			After another round of feedback, I found there were some organizational issues with the song modules. It appeared that the poster’s comment was the title of the song, which can be disorienting if the title appears to be “love this song!” I rearranged the header section of the song module to put the person’s name first, then their comment.
		</p>
		<p>The use of color was too intense and provided too strong of an emphasis on the emotion and the buttons in each module. I decided to tone this down and instead use color to highlight the leading comment. There was also not a strong visual indicator on how to select the songs. I envisioned the whole module to be clickable, but that is not clear at first glance. Other critiques involved the crowdedness of the module — I should spread out the information and make clear what I want to be clear.
		</p>
